objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of faricimab 6 mg IVT Q4W compared with aflibercept 2 mg IVT Q4W

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective Part 1
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of faricimab compared with aflibercept through Week 24

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective Part 2
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of faricimab administered according to the PTI dosing regimen from Week 24 through Week 72

objectives.name: Exploratory Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of faricimab on the basis of retinal ischemia and vascular leakage

endpoints.name: Primary Efficacy Endpoint
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in BCVA at Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 1
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in BCVA at specified timepoints through Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 2
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients gaining >=15 letters in BCVA from baseline at Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 3
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients gaining >=15, >=10, >=5, or >0 letters in BCVA from baseline at specified timepoints through Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 4
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients avoiding a loss of >=15, >=10, >=5, or >0 letters in BCVA from baseline at specified timepoints through Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 5
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients achieving >=84 letters (20/20 Snellen equivalent) in BCVA at specified timepoints through Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 6
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients with BCVA Snellen equivalent of 20/40 or better at specified timepoints through Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 7
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients with BCVA Snellen equivalent of 20/200 or worse at specified timepoints through Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 8
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in central subfield thickness (CST) at specified timepoints through Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 9
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in National Eye Institute 25-Item Visual Functioning Questionnaire (NEI VFQ-25) composite score at specified timepoints through Week 24

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 10
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in BCVA at specified timepoints from Week 24 through Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 11
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients gaining >=15 letters in BCVA from baseline at Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 12
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients gaining >=15, >=10, >=5, or >0 letters in BCVA from baseline at specified timepoints from Week 24 through Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 13
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients avoiding a loss of >=15, >=10, >=5, or >0 letters in BCVA from baseline at specified timepoints from Week 24 through Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 14
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients achieving >=84 letters (20/20 Snellen equivalent) in BCVA at specified timepoints from Week 24 through Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 15
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients with BCVA Snellen equivalent of 20/40 or better at specified timepoints from Week 24 through Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 16
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients with BCVA Snellen equivalent of 20/200 or worse at specified timepoints from Week 24 through Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 17
endpoints.text: Change from Week 24 in BCVA at specified timepoints through Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 18
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients avoiding a loss of >=15, >=10, >=5, or >0 letters in BCVA from Week 24 through Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 19
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients on a Q4W, every 8 weeks (Q8W), every 12 weeks (Q12W), or Q16W treatment interval at Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 20
endpoints.text: Number of study drug injections received from Week 24 through Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 21
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in CST at specified timepoints from Week 24 through Week 72

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint 22
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in NEI VFQ-25 composite score at specified timepoints from Week 24 through Week 72

endpoints.name: Exploratory Efficacy Endpoint 1
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients with absence of retinal ischemia on fundus fluorescein angiography (FFA) and on optical coherence tomography angiography (OCT-A) (optional) over time (at specified timepoints)

endpoints.name: Exploratory Efficacy Endpoint 2
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in area of retinal ischemia on FFA and on OCT-A (optional) over time

endpoints.name: Exploratory Efficacy Endpoint 3
endpoints.text: Proportion of patients with vascular leakage on FFA and on OCT-A (optional) over time

endpoints.name: Exploratory Efficacy Endpoint 4
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in area of vascular leakage on FFA, and on OCT-A (optional) over time

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with macular edema secondary to branch retinal vein occlusion (ITT population) Summary measure: Difference in least squares means.

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject discontinues study drug prior to Week 24

intercurrentEvents.name: Use of rescue medication
intercurrentEvents.text: Use of prohibited ocular treatments or rescue therapy

intercurrentEvents.name: Death
intercurrentEvents.text: Death of the patient prior to Week 24
